{{tocright}}
There are several messages starting with '''"You feel"''' that are associated with various features and attributes of ''[[NetHack]]''. These messages are generated by means of the text output function <tt>You_feel</tt>.{{refsrc|src/pline.c|319|nethack=3.6.7}} If the character is [[sleeping]] or [[fainted]], the message will instead start with '''"You dream that you feel"'''.

==Intrinsic and extrinsic feelings==
The following messages are associated with [[intrinsic]]s and extrinsics.

===Aggravate monster===
{{message|You feel that eating <creature> was a bad idea.|You gained the intrinsic permanently by eating a [[cat]] or [[dog]], unless you are an [[orc (monster class)|orc]] or [[Caveman]].}}
{{message|You feel less attractive.|You lost the intrinsic due to a [[gremlin]] attacking you at [[night]].}}

===Disintegration resistance===
{{message|You feel very firm.|You gained [[disintegration resistance]] from eating an appropriate [[corpse]], e.g. that of a [[black dragon]].}}
{{message|You feel totally together, man.|As above, while [[hallucinating]].}}

===Warning===
{{message|You feel sensitive!|You gained the [[warning]] intrinsic after reaching the appropriate [[experience level]] (i.e. XL 7 as a [[Monk]], or XL 15 as a Caveman, [[Healer]], [[Priest]], or [[Wizard]]).}}
{{message|You feel less sensitive!|You lost the intrinsic due to [[level drain]].}}

===Poison resistance===
{{message|You feel healthy.|You acquired [[poison resistance]] from reaching XL 3 as a [[Monk]], or from eating an appropriate corpse (e.g. [[quasit]], [[killer bee]]); the former will add an exclamation point.}}
{{message|You feel especially healthy.|As above, but you had extrinsic poison resistance from another worn object.}}
{{message|You feel hardy!|You reached XL 20 as a [[Tourist]].}}
{{message|You feel a little sick!|You lost the intrinsic due to level drain or a gremlin attack.}}

===Fire resistance===
{{message|You feel a momentary chill.|You gained the [[fire resistance]] intrinsic from eating an appropriate corpse (e.g. [[fire giant]]).}}
{{message|You be chillin'.|As above, while hallucinating.}}
{{message|You feel cool!|You gained the intrinsic by reaching XL 11 as a Monk, or XL 20 as a Priest.}}
{{message|You feel warmer.|You lost the intrinsic due a to a gremlin attack, eating a [[disenchanter]] corpse, or level drain (which adds an exclamation point).}}
{{message|You don't feel hot!|You were hit by a ray of fire (e.g. [[hell hound]], [[wand of fire]]) with fire resistance.}}
{{message|The fire doesn't feel hot!|You were hit by a monster's fire-element melee attack (e.g. [[fire ant]]) with fire resistance.}}
{{message|You feel rather warm.|You zapped yourself with a ray from a wand of fire or [[fire horn]] with fire resistance.}}
{{message|You feel mildly warm.|You were hit with a passive fire attack (e.g. [[red mold]]) with fire resistance.}}
{{message|You feel mildly hot.|A monster [[engulfing]] you tried to do fire damage (e.g. [[steam vortex]]), but you have fire resistance.}}
{{message|You're enveloped in flames. But you resist the effects.|You were hit by a monster's fire spell while having fire resistance. The <tt>AD_FIRE</tt> monster spell type is [[deferred]] in vanilla ''NetHack'', making this message impossible to see normally; you may see it in [[SLASH'EM]] as the result of [[fire vampire]]s using the spell.}}
{{message|It seems quite tasty.|You [[quaff]]ed from a [[sink]] and got scalding hot water, but you have fire resistance.}}
{{message|You are hit by molten lava.|A nearby [[boulder]] falling into [[lava]] splashes it on you, but you have fire resistance. Without resistance, this message has an exclamation mark instead.}}
{{message|Oh look, what a pretty fire in your <hands>.|You read a [[scroll of fire]] while [[confused]], and you have fire resistance.}}
{{message|You feel a pleasant warmth in your <hands>.|As above while [[blind]].}}
{{message|You aren't hurt!|Something in your inventory being destroyed (e.g. wand destroyed by [[lightning]]) does fire damage, but you have fire resistance.}}

===Cold resistance===
{{message|You feel full of hot air.|You gained the [[cold resistance]] intrinsic from eating an appropriate corpse (e.g. [[winter wolf]], [[yeti]]).}}
{{message|You feel warm!|You gained the intrinsic by reaching XL 13 as a Monk.}}
{{message|You feel cooler.|You lost the intrinsic to a gremlin attack or level drain; the latter will add an exclamation point.}}
{{message|You don't feel cold.|You were hit by a ray of cold (e.g. winter wolf, [[wand of cold]]) with cold resistance.}}
{{message|The frost doesn't seem cold!|You were hit by a monster's cold-element melee attack (e.g. the touch attack of [[Lich (monster class)|liches]]) with cold resistance.}}
{{message|[[You feel a little chill]].|You zapped yourself with a ray of cold with cold resistance.}}
{{message|You feel a mild chill.|You were hit by a passive cold attack (e.g. [[blue jelly]]) with cold resistance.}}
{{message|You feel mildly chilly.|A monster engulfing you dealt cold damage (i.e. [[ice vortex]]), but you have cold resistance.}}
{{message|You're covered in frost. But you resist the effects.|You were hit by a monster's cold spell (i.e. [[Asmodeus]]) with cold resistance.}}

===Sleep resistance===
{{message|You feel wide awake.|You gained the [[sleep resistance]] intrinsic from eating the appropriate corpse (e.g. any kind of [[elf]]).}}
{{message|You feel awake!|You gained the intrinsic by reaching XL 4 as an [[elf (starting race)|elf]].}}
{{message|You feel tired!|You lost the intrinsic due to level drain or a gremlin attack; this is not to be confused with the same message from a [[#Magic traps|magic trap]].}}

===Shock resistance===
{{message|Your health currently feels amplified!|You gained the [[shock resistance]] intrinsic from eating an appropriate corpse (e.g. [[electric eel]], [[storm giant]]).}}
{{message|You feel grounded in reality.|As above while hallucinating.}}
{{message|You feel insulated!|You gained the intrinsic by reaching XL 15 as a Monk.}}
{{message|You feel conductive!|You lost the intrinsic due to a gremlin attack or level drain.}}
{{message|You feel a mild tingle.|You were hit by shock damage from a passive attack or engulfing monster (e.g. [[energy vortex]]) with shock resistance.}}

===Invisible===
{{message|You feel hidden!|You permanently gained the [[invisibility]] and [[see invisible]] intrinsics by eating a [[stalker]] corpse while already (temporarily) invisible.}}
{{message|You feel rather itchy under your mummy wrapping.|You attempted to become invisible while wearing a [[mummy wrapping]].}}

===See invisible===
{{message|You see an image of someone stalking you. But it disappears.|You gained the [[see invisible]] intrinsic by [[quaffing]] from a fountain. Wisdom is exercised.}}
{{message|You feel very self-conscious. But it passes.|As above while blind.}}
{{message|You feel transparent.|As above while blind and also invisible.}}

{{message|Your vision becomes clear!|You gained the intrinsic from [[sitting]] on a [[throne]].}}
{{message|You thought you saw something!|You lost the intrinsic to a gremlin attack.}}
{{message|You tawt you taw a puttie tat!|As above while hallucinating.}}

===Protection===
{{message|You feel vulnerable.|You lost intrinsic [[protection]] to a gremlin attack.}}

===Searching===
{{message|You feel perceptive!|You gained [[automatic searching]] from reaching XL 9 as a Monk, or XL 10 as an [[Archaeologist]], [[Rogue]], or Tourist.}}

===Speed===
{{message|You feel quick!|You gained intrinsic speed by reaching XL 7 as a [[Barbarian]], Caveman, [[Knight]], or [[Valkyrie]].}}
{{message|Your quickness feels more natural.|You gained intrinsic speed from a [[wand of speed monster]] while wearing [[speed boots]].}} 
{{message|You feel slow!|You lost intrinsic speed as a result of level drain.}}

===Teleportitis===
{{message|You feel very jumpy.|You gained the [[teleportitis]] intrinsic from eating an appropriate corpse (e.g. any [[nymph]]).}}
{{message|You feel diffuse.|As above while halluncinating.}}
{{message|You feel less jumpy.|You lost the intrinsic due to a gremlin attack.}}

===Teleport control===
{{message|You feel controlled!|You gained intrinsic [[teleport control]] by reaching XL 17 as a Wizard or Monk.}}
{{message|You feel uncontrolled!|You lost the intrinsic through [[level drain]].}}
{{message|You feel in control of yourself.|You gained the teleport control intrinsic from eating an appropriate corpse (e.g. [[tengu]]).}}
{{message|You feel centered in your personal space.|As above while hallucinating.}}

===Telepathy===
{{message|You feel a strange mental acuity.|You gained intrinsic [[telepathy]] from eating an appropriate corpse (e.g. [[floating eye]]).}}
{{message|You feel in touch with the cosmos.|As above while hallucinating.}}

==Character properties==
The following are associated with [[attribute]]s and player traits.

===Character stats===
====[[Strength]]====
{{message|You feel <very> strong!|You gained one or more points of [[strength]], e.g. from [[exercise]], a [[potion of gain ability]] or eating a fresh [[giant]] corpse.}}
{{message|You feel <very> weak!|You lost one or more points of strength, e.g. as a result of [[abuse]] or sitting on a throne.}}
{{message|You suddenly feel weaker!|You were hit by the [[drain strength]] monster spell and lost strength. This is still displayed even if the stat loss is blocked through a [[ring of sustain ability]].}}
{{message|You feel momentarily weakened.|As above, but you have [[magic resistance]] and are completely unaffected.}}
{{message|You feel weaker.|You lost one or more points of strength from quaffing a non-[[blessed]] [[potion of sickness]].}}

====Dexterity====
{{message|You feel <very> agile!|You gained one or more points of [[dexterity]], e.g. through exercise or a potion of gain ability.}}
{{message|You feel <very> clumsy!|You lost one or more points of dexterity, e.g. as a result of abuse or sitting on a throne.}}

====Constitution====
{{message|You feel <very> tough!|You gained one or more points of [[constitution]], e.g. through exercise or a potion of gain ability.}}
{{message|You feel <very> fragile!|You lost one or more points of constitution, e.g. as a result of abuse or sitting on a throne.}}
{{message|You feel very sick.|You lost one or more points of constitution from quaffing a non-blessed potion of sickness.}}

====Intelligence====
{{message|You feel <very> smart!''|You gained one or more points of [[intelligence]], e.g. through exercise or a potion of gain ability.}}
{{message|You feel <very> stupid!''|You lost one or more points of intelligence, e.g. as a result of abuse, [[mind flayer]] attack, or sitting on a throne.}}
{{message|You feel like a scarecrow.|You died of [[brainlessness]] from a brain-eating attack landing while your intelligence is 3 in explore or wizard mode, but chose not to die. This sets your intelligence to 5, minus up to 2 points from the successful brain-eating attack that would have killed you.}}

====Wisdom====
{{message|You feel <very> wise!|You gained one or more points of [[wisdom]], e.g. through exercise or a potion of gain ability.}}
{{message|You feel <very> foolish!|You lost one or more points of wisdom, e.g. as a result of abuse or sitting on a throne.}}

====Charisma====
{{message|You feel <very> charismatic!''|You gained one or more points of [[charisma]], e.g. through exercise or a potion of gain ability.}}
{{message|You feel <very> repulsive!''|You lost one or more points of charisma, e.g. as a result of abuse or sitting on a throne.}}

===[[Skill]]===
{{message|You feel more confident in your weapon skills.|You practiced a weapon skill enough, and can now [[enhance]] it.}}
{{message|You feel more confident in your spell casting skills.|You practiced a spell-casting skill enough, and can now enhance it.}}
{{message|You feel more confident in your fighting skills|You practiced a combat skill enough, and can now enhance it.}}
{{message|You feel more confident in your skills.|You gained a skill slot by gaining a level, and can now enhance a sufficiently practiced skill.}}
{{message|You feel you could be more dangerous!|After enhancing a skill, you can enhance it or skills further.}}

===Statuses===

====Amnesia====
{{message|You feel like you've been here before.''|You entered a part of the dungeon that you have forgotten due to a [[scroll of amnesia]] or a successful brain-eating attack.}}
{{upcoming|3.7.0|This message may also occur when you enter a level where you left [[bones]].}}

====Confusion====
{{message|You feel somewhat dizzy.|You were hit and [[confused]] by a thrown [[potion of confusion]] or [[potion of booze]].}}
{{message|You feel confused.|You were confused from reading a [[cursed]] [[scroll of confuse monster]], or read any such scroll while [[polymorph]]ed into any non-{{monclasssym|@}}, [[TDTTOE|confusing your monster form]]).}}
{{message|You feel rather light headed.|You were confused as a result of [[rotten food]].}}
{{message|You feel rather trippy.|As above while hallucinating.}}
{{message|You feel less confused now.|You are no longer confused.}}
{{message|You feel less trippy now.|As above while hallucinating.}}

====Lycanthropy====
{{message|You feel feverish.|You have contracted [[lycanthropy]] from a [[werecreature]].}}
{{message|You feel purified.|You have been cured of lycanthropy.}}

====Sickness====
{{message|You feel deathly sick.|You have contracted [[sickness]] from [[food poisoning]] or a source of [[illness]].}}
{{message|You feel sick.|You narrowly avoided sickness from food poisoning, and lost 1d8 hit points.}}
{{message|You feel even worse.<br>You feel much worse.|You were hit by a disease attack or contracted illness by other means when already sick, reducing your 'time to live' counter to half of its old value.}}
{{message|You feel somewhat better.|You cured food poisoning by [[vomiting]], but are still suffering from illness. Your 'time to live' counter is doubled.}}
{{message|You are feeling mildly nauseated.|You developed nausea from eating a cursed [[tin]], a rotten [[egg]], a [[tripe ration]] (unless you are an orc or Caveman), or a [[clove of garlic]] while polymorphed into an [[undead]] form. This message prints when you have 14 turns of nausea timeout left.}}
{{message|You feel slightly confused.|As above, but with 11 turns left; you only actually become confused for 2d4 (more) turns when the timeout reaches 8, then 6.}}
{{message|You feel much less nauseated now.|You are no longer nauseated, e.g. after curing yourself with a unicorn horn.}}

====Stoning====
{{message|You feel limber!|You were cured of [[stoning]], e.g. by eating a [[lizard]] corpse.}}

====Stunned====
{{message|You feel a bit steadier now.|You recovered from being [[stunned]].}}
{{message|You feel less wobbly now.|As above while hallucinating.}}

===Conducts and alignment===
{{message|You feel like a hypocrite.|You attacked while over an [[Elbereth]] engraving. This only occurs as of [[NetHack 3.6.0]]; it carries a -5 alignment penalty and makes the engraving disappear.}}
{{message|You feel like an evil coward for using a poisoned weapon.|You hit with a poisoned weapon as a [[lawful]] character, which carries an -1 alignment penalty.}}
{{message|You feel like a despicable grave-robber!|As a lawful Archaeologist, you dug up a [[grave]].}}
{{message|You feel guilty about damaging such a historic statue.|As an Archaeologist, you broke a [[historic statue]].}}
{{message|You feel like a glutton!|As a Knight, you ate while [[satiated]], incurring a -1 alignment penalty for violating the [[Knight#Code of conduct|code of conduct]].}}
{{message|You feel like a common thief.|As a Knight, you dug down while in a shop, and the shopkeeper was still alive.}}

====Altars and sacrifice====
{{message|You feel partially absolved.|You sacrificed a corpse at a co-aligned [[altar]] while your alignment was negative, increasing it up to a maximum of zero depending on the corpse.}}
{{message|You feel appropriately <your alignment>.|You sacrificed a cross-aligned [[unicorn]] at a co-aligned altar.}}
{{message|You feel you are thoroughly on the right path.|As above, but your alignment was at maximum.}}
{{message|You feel an urge to return to the surface.|You offered the [[Amulet of Yendor]] or its [[Cheap plastic imitation of the Amulet of Yendor|cheap plastic imitation]] on a co-aligned non-[[high altar]].}}
{{message|You feel ashamed.|As above, but the altar was cross-aligned.}}
{{message|You feel homesick.|You were hallucinating in either of the above cases.}}
{{message|Unluckily, you feel the power of <your god> decrease.|You sacrificed a corpse at a cross-aligned non-high altar, but the altar was not converted; this abuses your wisdom and you lose a point of Luck.}}
{{message|You feel the power of <your god> increase.|As above, but you successfully converted the altar to your alignment.}}

====Prayer====
{{message|You feel in good health again.|You [[pray]]ed successfully and restored one or more [[attribute]]s that had been lowered.}}

===Other properties===
{{message|You feel self-knowledgeable.|You were [[enlightenment|enlightened]], e.g. by using a [[wand of enlightenment|wand]] or [[potion of enlightenment]].}}

==Dungeon features==
The following are associated with [[dungeon features]]s.

===Traps===
====Anti-magic traps====
{{message|You feel your magical energy drain away.|You stepped on an [[anti-magic trap]] and your [[energy]] was drained.}}
{{message|You feel momentarily lethargic.|As above, but your maximum energy was already 0.}}
{{message|You feel sluggish.|You stepped on an anti-magic trap, but had magic resistance and instead took damage that was less than {{frac|4}} of your HP.}}
{{message|You feel very lethargic.|As above, but the resulting damage was at least {{frac|4}} of your HP.}}
{{message|You feel unbearably torpid!|As above, but you were killed by the implosion from HP loss.}}

====Magic traps====
{{message|You feel rankled.|You triggered a [[magic trap]] and it created monsters around you after blinding and [[deaf]]ening you, but you were already deaf beforehand; the deafness is extended for 1d5 + 15 more turns.}}
{{message|You feel tired.|This is one of six "odd feeling" results from stepping on a magic trap, all of which produce different messages with no effect. It is distinct from the message given for losing sleep resistance (see [[#Intrinsic and extrinsic feelings|"Intrinsic and extrinsic feelings"]] above).}}
{{message|You feel [oddly] like the prodigal son.|"Yearning for your homeland" is another "odd feeling", and you got it while already on the home level of your [[quest]]. Female characters feel "oddly".}}
{{message|You feel charismatic!|You stepped on a magic trap and gained a point of charisma. All adjacent tameable monsters are [[tame]]d, and non-tameable monsters are made peaceful; this ignores [[Magic resistance (monster)|monster MR]].}}

====Polymorph traps====
{{message|You feel momentarily different.|You stepped on a polymorph trap, but had magic resistance or were wearing an [[amulet of unchanging]].}}

===Doors, walls and corridors===
{{message|You feel a draft.|A monster has tunneled through a secret corridor, or a secret door was detected on the [[Rogue level]].{{refsrc|src/dig.c|1292|nethack=3.6.7}}}}
{{message|You feel like <enlisting/marching/protesting/fleeing>.|As above while hallucinating.}}
{{message|[[You feel an unexpected draft]].|A monster has broken through a door.}}
{{message|You feel like you are 1-A/4-F.|As above while hallucinating.}}
{{message|You feel more claustrophobic than before!|You were in a [[shop]] while the [[shopkeeper]] magically repaired the wall, but you were blind.}}

===Fountains===
{{message|You feel a sudden chill.|One possible "no effect" message of [[dip]]ping into a [[fountain]].}}
{{message|You feel the presence of evil.|You summoned a [[water demon]] by quaffing from or dipping into a fountain while blind.}}

===Sitting on thrones===
In addition to the [[#Character stats|attribute loss messages]] and other previously mentioned throne messages, the following may also occur: 
{{message|You feel a strange sensation.|You would have lost your money, but your wallet had no gold.}}
{{message|You feel much, much better!|Your HP is fully restored, which may also increase your maximum HP; this cures blinding, sickness and wounded legs.}}
{{message|You feel your luck is changing.|You gain a point of [[Luck]]; if your natural Luck is high enough, this effect is replaced with a [[wish]].}}
{{message|You feel somehow out of place...|No effect.}}
{{message|You feel very comfortable here.|As above, but you are polymorphed into a [[queen bee]], [[gnome king]], [[dwarf king]], [[ogre king]] or [[Elvenking]].}}

==Items==
The following are associated with item usage.

===Armor===
{{message|You feel like sitting in a corner.|You put on a [[dunce cap]], and your intelligence was greater than or equal to 6; the cap autocurses, fixes your intelligence and wisdom at 6, and prevents any changes to them. Removing the cap will restore those stat to their original values.}}
{{message|You feel giddy.|As above, but your intelligence was less than 6.}}

===Potions===
{{message|You feel completely healed.|You quaffed a potion of full healing.}}
{{message|You feel lackluster.|You quaffed a cursed [[potion of gain energy]].}}
{{message|You feel lonely.|You quaffed a blessed [[potion of monster detection]], but there were no other monsters on the level.}}
{{message|You feel a lack of something.|You quaffed a [[potion of object detection]], and remembered objects that were on the map are now gone.}}
{{message|You feel a little strange.|You quaffed a [[potion of polymorph]].}}
{{message|You feel a little normal.|As above, while hallucinating.}}
{{message|You feel rather tired.|You inhaled vapors from a [[potion of sleeping]].}}

====Potion of water====
{{message|You feel full of awe.|You drank [[holy water]] and you were not polymorphed into a [[major demon]] or [[undead]] monster.}}
{{message|You feel quite proud of yourself.|You drank unholy water while chaotic, a demon, or undead.}}
{{message|You feel full of dread.|As above, but you were of a different alignment and not polymorphed into a demon or undead.}}

===Scrolls===
{{message|You feel charged up!|You read a non-cursed [[scroll of charging]] while confused.}}
{{message|You feel discharged|As above, but the scroll was cursed.}}
{{message|You have a feeling of loss.|You attempted to charge an non-chargeable item.}}
{{message|You feel very greedy.|You read a cursed [[scroll of gold detection]], and there are traps on the level.}}

===Tools===
{{message|You feel rushing air tickle your nose.|You applied a [[tin whistle]] while deaf.}}

===Wands===
{{message|You feel vibrations.|A beam-type wand was zapped, but it was blocked by a door while out of your sight.}}

==Other magical effects==
===Aggravate monsters===
:''Note that this is different from the actual "aggravate monster" intrinsic; see [[aggravate monster|that article]] for more details.''
{{message|You feel that monsters are aware of your presence.|You quaffed a cursed potion of invisibility, or a nearby monster has cast the [[aggravate monster]] [[monster spell|spell]]. This wakes up all sleeping monsters on the level, and there is a one-fifth chance that paralyzed monsters are unparalyzed. The Wizard of Yendor may also invoke this effect as a means of remote harassment.}}
{{message|You feel aggravated at the invisible <monster>.|A monster drank a cursed potion of invisibility; this will reveal its location to you.}}

===Conflict===
{{message|You feel like a rabble-rouser.|You [[invoked]] [[the Sceptre of Might]] and are now causing [[conflict]].}}
{{message|You feel the tension decrease around you.|You invoked the Sceptre of Might (or it left your main inventory), and you are no longer causing conflict.}}
{{message|You feel a surge of power, but nothing happens.|You invoked the Sceptre, but you were already causing conflict by other means, e.g. a [[ring of conflict]].}}

===Curses===
{{message|[[You feel like someone is helping you]].|The phrase occurs with many instances of curse removal - this includes reading any [[scroll of remove curse]], casting the [[spell of remove curse]], and stepping on a magic trap and getting the [[remove curse]] effect, which is the same as an uncursed scroll. This applies even if no items were cursed.}}
{{message|You feel like you need some help.|You read a noncursed scroll of remove curse while confused.}}
{{message|You feel as if you need some help.|A monster has used the [[curse items]] spell against you, and attempted to curse something in your inventory.}}
{{message|You feel a malignant aura surround you.|The spell cursed at least one random item in your inventory.}}
{{message|You feel a malignant aura surround the magic-absorbing blade.|As above, but [[Magicbane]] caught and absorbed the curse; it will resist with a {{frac|19|20}} chance.}}

===Genocide===
{{message|You feel dead inside.|You [[genocide]]d your original race or role while polymorphed into another form.}}

===Healing===
{{message|You feel better.|You quaffed a [[potion of healing]] or cast the {{spell of|healing}} spell at yourself.}}
{{message|You feel much better.|You quaffed a [[potion of extra healing]], cast the {{spell of|extra healing}} spell at yourself, or had HP restored from prayer.}}

===Phasing===
{{message|You feel much slimmer.|As a result of [[prayer]], you temporarily gained the ability to pass through walls. This happens if you were stuck in a wall, but there was no safe place to teleport you to.{{refsrc|src/pray.c|432|nethack=3.6.7}}}}
{{message|You feel hemmed in again.|Your temporary phasing power wore off, and you are still stuck in a wall.}}

===Polymorphing===
{{message|You feel a change coming over you.|You are polymorphing as a result of eating a [[chameleon]] or [[doppelganger]] corpse, or stepping on a polymorph trap.}}
{{message|You feel rather <monster>-ish.|You tried to polymorph into a monster form that has been genocided.}}
{{message|You feel like a new <race>!|You [[polymorph#Polymorphing into your own race|polymorphed into your own race]].}}
{{message|You feel like a new <monster>!|You polymorphed into a monster while already being that monster; this is treated as returning to your normal form, then immediately resuming your previous form.}}

{{message|[[You feel shuddering vibrations]].|You polymorphed a pile of items (armor, corpses, gold and/or scrolls) with a [[wand of polymorph|wand]] or spell of {{spell of|polymorph}}.}}

===Teleporting===
{{message|You feel a wrenching sensation.|You stepped on a [[teleport trap]] or [[level teleport trap]] trap while magic resistant, sat on a throne and got the teleportation effect, or else failure to read a [[spellbook]] caused a teleportation effect.}} 
{{message|You feel disoriented for a moment.|An attempt to teleport or branchport failed for some reason, e.g. interference from the Amulet of Yendor.}}

==Monsters==
The following messages are associated with various types of monsters.

===Pets===
{{message|You feel worried about <your <pet>>.|Your pet's [[nutrition]] is low enough that it is starving, and the pet is out of your sight; a starving pet becomes confused from hunger, its maximum HP is temporarily reduced to 1/4 of its current value, and it will die in 250 turns unless fed, which restores its maximum HP (but not its current HP) to normal.{{refsrc|src/dogmove.c|380|nethack=3.6.7}}}}
{{message|You feel sad for a moment.|Your pet starved to death while out of your sight.}}
{{message|You feel guilty losing your pet like this.|You displaced your pet into a trap, killing it; this incurs a -15 alignment penalty and [[anger]]s your god.}}

===[[Foocubus#Messages|Foocubus]] encounters===
{{message|You feel good enough to do it again.|You gained a point of constitution, also exercising constitution.}}
{{message|You feel restored to health.|You were healed to maximum HP, and strength is exercised.}}
{{message|You feel raised to your full potential.|You were restored to maximum energy, and your maximum energy was also increased by 1-5 points; constitution is exercised.}}
{{message|You feel exhausted.|You take 10-16 hit points of damage, and strength is abused.}}
{{message|You feel drained of energy.|Your maximum energy is decreased by 1-10 points, and your energy is set to zero; constitution is abused.}}
{{message|You feel out of shape.|You lose an experience level, unless you have [[drain resistance]].}}

===Werecreatures===
{{message|You feel hemmed in!|A werecreature called for help while you were blind or already surrounded by monsters, and one or more of them spawned out of your sight.}}

===The Wizard of Yendor===
{{message|You feel vaguely nervous.|The [[Wizard of Yendor]] did not harass you during an eligible turn.}}

===Corpses===
{{message|You feel a mild buzz.|You gained energy or increased your maximum energy by eating a [[newt]] corpse.}}
{{message|You feel squirming in your backpack!|A [[Troll (monster class)|troll]] revived from its corpse while it was in your inventory.}}

==Other phrases with multiple sources==
{{message|You feel threatened.|You failed to read a spellbook and woke up all sleeping monsters on the level, unparalyzing paralyzed monsters; sat on a throne and produced the aggravate monster effect; quaffed a non-blessed potion of monster detection when there were no other monsters on the level; or quaffed from a fountain and would have been shown monsters on the level, but there were none.}}
{{message|[[You feel guilty]].|You ate non-[[vegetarian]] food as a Monk and incurred a -1 alignment penalty, killed a co-aligned unicorn and suffered a -5 Luck penalty, or else read a blessed [[scroll of punishment]] (which has no effect).}}

==Miscellaneous==
{{message|You feel besieged.|You are hemmed in by monsters during the [[Endgame]].}}

